	)
	(text "I found Google's Gemini AI tool to be extremely helpful during \nthis design process. Especially with mapping the pinout of the \ndisplay to STM32. I used a cheap knockoff with no documentation \nand poor pinout labels. \n\nIn the future may need to remap pins if display fails to work.\n\nSee ARSensors project for 2nd Board meant to connect sensors to this\nmain board."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 157.48 146.05 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.1588)
			)
